      "message": "Frame class doesn\u0027t look like a big thing - it\u0027s 32 bytes now and you can make it to be only 24 bytes big. This way you would save an extra heap allocation - moving a Frame into and out of the message channel is pretty much the same as moving a pointer\n\nyou could also use Optional\u003c\u003e to not change the code much:\n\nOptional\u003cFrame\u003e f;\nif (...)\n   f.emplace(\u003cconstructor parameters\u003e);\n\nif (f)\n   channel.trySend(std::move(*f));",
