      "writtenOn": "2017-11-30T19:40:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this isn\u0027t guaranteed to sleep as much as you\u0027ve specified. MSDN explicitly states that ::Sleep() API may sleep both less and more than requested\nTo have a precise delay please create a separate abstraction based on waitable timers - https://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/windows/desktop/ms687012(v\u003dvs.85).aspx\n\nBoth Linux and Mac also need some more fine-tuned functions for precise sleeps and to deal with signals:\n\nhttps://linux.die.net/man/3/clock_nanosleep\nhttps://github.com/ChisholmKyle/PosixMachTiming",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 151,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 152,
        "endChar": 62
      },
      "revId": "39acf2124978ec9eccb9a5a25887ac9ec5e99895",
